Male
. 
Genitalia
. Tergite X elongate, tubular, about as long as pygofer (
Figs 16a, 16b
), ventrally with small, circular recess. Pygofer with wide anterior apodeme; pygofer lobe membranous, digitate, slightly curved dorsomedially (
Fig. 16b
). Valve semicircular, with small anterior apodeme (
Fig. 16c
). Subgenital plate elongate, length to width ratio 1.36–1.75 (n=6), apex narrowly rounded (
Fig. 16c
), medial margin divergent, about 5°, lateral margin uniformly curvate. Aedeagus with shaft elongate, straight, sclerotized in basal two-thirds, membranous apex (
Fig. 16e
); dorsal apodeme complex, narrowly joined to shaft, positioned dorsad of shaft. Dorsal apodeme of aedeagus with posteriad paired tooth, curvate dorsoposteriad, anteriorly with elongate arms (
Figs 16d, 16e
). Aedeagal paraphysis tubular, apex acute, extending beyond aedeagal shaft (
Fig. 16e
), fused subbasally (
Fig. 16f
). Style apophysis in dorsal view digitate, curvate (
Fig. 16h
), in lateral view digitate (

Fig. 
16g

), angled dorsoposteriad; preapical lobe obtuse (

Fig. 
16g

); style situated near base of subgenital plate. Connective with transverse section convex and arms curvate (

Fig. 
16i

).
